HEADWORD: escargot
<hw>es`car*got"</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧s`k⟦aum⟧r*g⟦omac⟧")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F. snail.]</ety> <def>any edible terrestrial snail prepared as
food; as a dish, it is usually served in the shell with a sauce of
melted butter and garlic.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> snail.</syn>⟦br⟧
